FBIS3-39658 "drweu034_q_94007" FBIS-WEU-94-034 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Feb 1994 TURKEY Government Draft Resolution Condemns Racism TA1702161894 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 17 Feb 94 TA1702161894 Ankara ANATOLIA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Ankara, Feb 17 (AA) -- Turkey on Thursday [17 February] proposed a draft resolution to Human Rights Commission which foresees struggle against racism and intolerance. Foreign Ministry officials told AA that the draft resolution will be presented during Human Rights Commission's meeting that will take place in Geneva on Friday. Officials said Turkey played a leading role against struggle with racism adding European Council accepted to initiate an action plan at a human rights summit on Oct 1993 in Vienna.
